parameters: What!? A group of slimes!? Are you trying to get
killed!? \n< Serena >

Heheheheheh... \n< ??? >

you and you're running away? \n< ??? >

...ugh... \n< Serena >
...Oh...scary...indeed scary. Slimes are...yeah. \n< Serena >
Heh heh heh? Then what are you going to do? Besides
running away with your tail between your legs, do you
have any other options, huh? \n< Guy >
Well...I do feel like running away. \n< Serena >
It took considerable courage to come this far. \n< Serena >
But to be truthful, all of this is your fault. \n< Serena >
Hmm...? \n< Guy >
If we weigh anger and fear on a scale, anger is
currently slightly winning. \n< Serena >
That's why I can take a step forward. I can move
forward. I won't be satisfied until I strike you down. \n< Serena >
Hey kid, can you see my slime? \n< Guy >
I can see it. But I'll make it disappear quickly. \n< Serena >
...Are you Guy? \n< Serena >
Heh heh heh? Then what are you going to do? Besides
running away with your tail between your legs, do you
have any other options, huh? \n< Guy >
Hmm. \n< Serena >
The world is a vast place. Since coming to
this town, I've been constantly amazed. \n< Serena >
Hey...? \n< Guy >
I never imagined there would be humans who can
communicate with slimes. No wonder they can nest in
the sewers. \n< Serena >
Hey kid, can you see my slime? \n< Guy >
It's certainly visible, but it disappears quickly. \n< Serena >
No, I still can't see you! \n< Guy >

...Hiiyii... My slime friends... Ahh... My invincible
kingdom...! \n< Guy >

Ugh...hehe. \n< Guy >

Wow, you're so strong despite being young! Really
strong! Oh, I've witnessed it! \n< Guy >
What an upbeat guy... \n< Serena >
Hehehe... That's just my only strong point... \n< Guy >
*Sigh*... I used to think that adult men were
something worthy of more respect... \n< Serena >
Since coming to this town, I've only been increasingly
disappointed. Or is it that the people in this town
are just special? \n< Serena >
...Speaking of something special. How did you manage
to control the slime? \n< Serena >
I've never heard of such a skill. \n< Serena >
Huh?... Oh, no... Hehe, to control like that... I'm
not capable of anything... \n< Guy >
??? \n< Serena >
Hehehe... Well, just between you and me, Sister, shall
I tell you my trade secret? \n< Guy >
Sis... \n< Serena >

There's a little secret packed inside this bottle, you
know. \n< Guy >
If you have this, slimes won't attack me... I mean,
the owner... Well, to be precise, they won't attack
this bottle. \n< Guy >
Hmm... *sigh*...? \n< Serena >
Black liquid...? I wonder what it is? Some kind of
chemical? \n< Serena >
Oh, I see. That's how it is then. \n< Guy >
*Sigh*... However, this is not a major discovery. This
town should also be struggling with controlling the
slimes. \n< Serena >
How much easier would our struggles be with this
liquid? No, the ways to use it are endless... \n< Serena >
If there was something like this, I wouldn't have had
to be involved in the distribution of poison. \n< Serena >
We could have easily made a fortune worth millions. \n< Serena >
Oh no, this was something I picked up. I didn't make
it myself or anything. \n< Guy >
“Why only sell one bottle like this? Even if it sells,
it won't make much money, right?” \n< Guy >
Even if I were to use it for something, my head
wouldn't be able to handle it... \n< Guy >
So, did they decide to use the sewers to sell poison? \n< Serena >
This is an irredeemable foolishness. A discovery that
could change the world, being confined in such a cheap
bottle... \n< Serena >
No, no, here's the thing. The fact that this bottle is
cheap is just gross, you know? \n< Guy >
Hmm. \n< Serena >
This already looks shoddy and fragile just by looking
at it, doesn't it? That's why I'm doing it like this. \n< Guy >
I could throw it and make it a distraction! \n< Guy >
Huh!? \n< Serena >
